region.notes:
The North Oregon Cascades are part of a much larger mountain range that extends from British Columbia south into extreme southern California.  The Oregon Cascades are best known for their recreational opportunities with major, world-class ski resorts on Mt. Hood and Mt. Bachelor in the south to seven major national forests including Crater Lake National Park and the Oregon Caves National Monument.  

Most of the peaks in the Cascades can be dangerous and do experience life-threatening winter weather.
